===冰河形成===
扎格羅斯山脈東部的三個山峰，庫伊賈帕爾山（Kuh-i-Jupar，4,135公尺（13,566英尺）），庫伊拉萊薩爾山（Kuh-i-Lalezar，4,374公尺（14,350英尺））和庫伊赫扎爾山（Kuh-i-Hezar，4,469公尺（14,662英尺）），目前都沒有冰河。只有在{{link-en|扎德·庫山|Zard Kuh}}和[[德納山|德納山]]，仍有一些冰河存在。但是，在上個[[冰期|冰期]]之前的冰期，它們的冰河厚度超過1,900公尺（1.2英里），而在上個冰期期間，它們的冰河厚度則超過2,160公尺（7,090英尺）。有證據顯示曾有一條20公里（12英里）寬的冰川沿著一條17公里（11英里）長的山谷往下，沿庫伊賈帕爾山北側，落差達到約1,600公尺（5,200英尺），冰河厚度為350–550公尺（1,150–1,800英尺）。在與當前氣候記錄可比的降水條件下，可預期形成這種冰河的所在，年平均溫度應在攝氏10.5至11.2度（華氏50.9至52.2度）之間，但由於冰河形成當時的氣候條件屬於乾燥，那個時期的溫度應該會較低 <ref>Kuhle, M. (1974):''Vorläufige Ausführungen morphologischer Feldarbeitsergebnisse aus den SE-Iranischen Hochgebirgen am Beispiel des Kuh-i-Jupar.'' Zeitschrift für Geomorphologie N.F., 18, (4), pp. 472-483.</ref><ref>Kuhle, M. (1976):''Beiträge zur Quartärgeomorphologie SE-Iranischer Hochgebirge. Die quartäre Vergletscherung des Kuh-i-Jupar.'' Göttinger Geographische Abhandlungen, 67, Vol. I, pp. 1-209; Vol. II, pp. 1-105.</ref><ref>Kuhle, M. (2007):''The Pleistocene Glaciation (LGP and pre-LGP, pre-LGM) of SE-Iranian Mountains exemplified by the Kuh-i-Jupar, Kuh-i-Lalezar and Kuh-i-Hezar Massifs in the Zagros. '' Polarforschung, 77, (2-3), pp. 71-88. (Erratum/ Clarification concerning Figure 15, Vol. 78, (1-2), 2008, p. 83.</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Elsevier: Ehlers, |title=Quaternary Glaciations - Extent and Chronology Volume 15: A closer look Welcome |url=http://booksite.elsevier.com/9780444534477/ |website=booksite.elsevier.com |accessdate=2020-02-20 |archive-date=2013-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130606133044/http://booksite.elsevier.com/9780444534477/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==植物和動物==
{{Main|扎格羅斯山脈森林草原}}

{{multiple image
| align = right
| direction = vertical
| image1 = The environs of Borujerd (Goldasht).JPG
| caption1 = 佔扎格羅斯山脈樹種最多的{{link-en|波斯櫟|Quercus brantii}}森林一景
| width1 = 220
| image2 = Antoin Sevruguin 7 Men with live lion.jpg
| caption2 = 獵人和被捕獲獅子的合影，相片由[[卡扎爾王朝|卡扎爾王朝]]時期俄裔攝影家{{link-en|安妥英·薩夫魯秦|Antoin Sevruguin}}所拍攝（約在1880年，在伊朗亞洲獅滅絕之前作品）<ref name="Sevruguin">{{cite web |author=Sevruguin, A. |title=Men with live lion |publisher=National Museum of Ethnology in Leiden, The Netherlands; Stephen Arpee Collection |url=http://archive.asia.si.edu/iran-in-photographs/sevruguin-negatives.asp |date=1880 |access-date=2018-03-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180326202724/http://archive.asia.si.edu/iran-in-photographs/sevruguin-negatives.asp |archive-date=2018-03-26 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>
| width2 = 220
}}
目前扎格羅斯山脈地區因[[過度放牧|過度放牧]]和[[森林砍伐|森林砍伐]]而退化，但這裡仍然擁有豐富而複雜的植物。仍然可找到原始分佈的以[[櫟屬|橡樹]]為主的林地的殘餘，還有像公園一樣，種植[[開心果|開心果]]/[[扁桃|杏仁]]的[[乾草原|乾草原]]。在整個山區都可以發現野生，包含[[小麥|小麥]]、[[大麥|大麥]]、[[小扁豆|小扁豆]]、杏仁、[[核桃|核桃]]、[[開心果|開心果]]、{{link-en|杏|apricot}}、[[李亞屬|李]]、[[石榴|石榴]]、和[[葡萄|葡萄]]，他們是當前我們熟悉的食用植物的祖先。<ref>{{cite book|last=Cowan|first=edited by C. Wesley|title=The origins of agriculture : an international perspective|year=2006|publisher=University of Alabama Press|location=Tuscaloosa, Ala.|isbn=0-8173-5349-6|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Sl8w4FwWi48C&lpg=PT50&ots=UXs4_JVtCH&dq=pistachio%2Falmond%20steppe&pg=PT50#v=onepage&q=pistachio/almond%20steppe&f=false|edition=[New ed.].|author2=Nancy L. Benco|author3=Patty Jo Watson|accessdate=5 May 2012|archive-date=2020-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225130127/https://books.google.com/books?id=Sl8w4FwWi48C&lpg=PT50&ots=UXs4_JVtCH&dq=pistachio%2Falmond%20steppe&pg=PT50#v=onepage&q=pistachio/almond%20steppe&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{link-en|波斯櫟|Quercus brantii}}（西亞原生橡樹，佔扎格羅斯山脈森林面積的50％以上）是伊朗扎格羅斯山脈最重要的樹種。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://research.guilan.ac.ir/cjes/.papers/25210.pdf |title=Plant species in Oak (Quercus brantii Lindl.) understory and their relationship with physical and chemical propertiesof soil in different altitude classes in the Arghvan valley protected area, Iran |last1=M. Heydari |last2=H. Poorbabaei |last3=T. Rostami |last4=M. Begim Faghir |last5=A. Salehi |last6=R. Ostad Hashmei |year=2013 |website= |publisher=Caspian Journal of Environmental Sciences, 2013, Vol. 11 No.1, pp. 97~110 |accessdate=10 April 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403163132/http://research.guilan.ac.ir/cjes/.papers/25210.pdf |archivedate=3 April 2015}}</ref>
[[File:Leopard-Zom_village-Hawraman.jpg|thumb]]

在這個山脈中還可發現種類繁多的其他花卉[[特有種|特有種]]。 <ref>{{cite web |title=Haji Omran Mountain (IQ018) |url=http://www.natureiraq.org/uploads/9/2/7/0/9270858/haji_omran-iq018-sep-25-final.pdf |format=PDF |publisher=natrueiraq.org |accessdate=22 June 2016 |archive-date=2020-09-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200929202407/http://www.natureiraq.org/uploads/9/2/7/0/9270858/haji_omran-iq018-sep-25-final.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>

扎格羅斯山脈是許多受威脅或瀕臨滅絕動物的家園，包括{{link-en|扎格羅斯老鼠形倉鼠|Zagros Mountains mouse-like hamster}}（Calomyscus bailwardi）、{{link-en|巴士拉蘆葦鶯|Basra reed-warbler}}（Acrocephalus griseldis）、[[條紋鬣狗|條紋鬣狗]]、{{link-en|魯里斯坦蠑螈|Luristan newt}}（Neurergus kaiseri）-這些都是伊朗扎格羅斯山脈中部脆弱的[[特有種|特有種]]。[[波斯黇鹿|波斯黇鹿]]是一種曾被認為已滅絕的古老馴養動物，於20世紀後期在扎格羅斯山脈南部的[[胡齊斯坦省|胡齊斯坦省]]被重新發現。
[[File:Dasht-_Kahou,_Taq-e_Bostan.jpg|thumb]]境內的薩格羅斯山區，佈滿季節性青翠植物]]

19世紀末，[[亞洲獅|亞洲獅]]<ref name="CatSG2017">{{cite journal |author1=Kitchener, A. C. |author2=Breitenmoser-Würsten, C. |author3=Eizirik, E. |author4=Gentry, A. |author5=Werdelin, L. |author6=Wilting A. |author7=Yamaguchi, N. |author8=Abramov, A. V. |author9=Christiansen, P. |author10=Driscoll, C. |author11=Duckworth, J. W. |author12=Johnson, W. |author13=Luo, S.-J. |author14=Meijaard, E. |author15=O’Donoghue, P. |author16=Sanderson, J. |author17=Seymour, K. |author18=Bruford, M. |author19=Groves, C. |author20=Hoffmann, M. |author21=Nowell, K. |author22=Timmons, Z. |author23=Tobe, S. |year=2017 |title=A revised taxonomy of the Felidae: The final report of the Cat Classification Task Force of the IUCN Cat Specialist Group |journal=Cat News |volume=Special Issue 11 |url=http://www.catsg.org/fileadmin/filesharing/5.Cat_News/5.3._Special_Issues/5.3.10._SI_11/CN_Special_Issue_11_Revised_taxonomy_of_the_Felidae.pdf |access-date=2020-02-20 |archive-date=2017-07-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731185717/http://www.catsg.org/fileadmin/filesharing/5.Cat_News/5.3._Special_Issues/5.3.10._SI_11/CN_Special_Issue_11_Revised_taxonomy_of_the_Felidae.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref> 曾棲息在山脈的西南部，但現在已經滅絕。<ref name="HeptnerSludskiy1972">{{cite book |author1=Heptner, V. G. |author2=Sludskij, A. A. |orig-year=1972 |year=1992 |title=Mlekopitajuščie Sovetskogo Soiuza. Moskva: Vysšaia Škola |trans-title=Mammals of the Soviet Union. Volume II, Part 2. Carnivora (Hyaenas and Cats) |publisher=Smithsonian Institution and the National Science Foundation |location=Washington DC |chapter=Lion |chapter-url=https://archive.org/stream/mammalsofsov221992gept#page/83/mode/2up |url=https://archive.org/stream/mammalsofsov221992gept#page/n0/mode/2up |pages=82–95 |isbn=90-04-08876-8}}</ref>

==宗教==
傳說中{{le|遠古美索不達米亞冥界|Ancient Mesopotamian underworld}}的入口處是在紮格羅斯山脈的遙遠東部。<ref name="Black & Green 1992">{{citation|last1=Black|first1=Jeremy|first2=Anthony|last2=Green|title=Gods, Demons and Symbols of Ancient Mesopotamia: An Illustrated Dictionary|location=Austin, Texas|publisher=University of Texas Press|year=1992|isbn=0714117056|page=180}}</ref>通過大門循樓梯而下。<ref name="Black & Green 1992"/>冥界所在之處，比地底深埋淡水的[[阿勃祖|阿勃祖]]還要深。<ref name="Black & Green 1992"/>

